is it easier to conceive the third child hi i have two beautiful girls both of my girls were unplanned my husband and i have decided we would love to have another child i'm worried because it's been awhile since i've done this whole pregnancy thing this was our first month to try i have more days before i can take a pregnancy test for some reason i'm worried it won't happen i've looked it up and realized how hard it actually is to get pregnant i had sex on all the days necessary but was just wondering if it's easier to get pregnant the third time around my husband and i are on our th month ttc our previous pregnancy's were unplanned as well so we thought if it could just happen so many times before without planning then child could be conceived no problem ha a fool was i we are charting and using opk's to help with our attempt i know we are both fertile so i am aware it is just a matter of time best of luck to you there is a book called taking charge of your fertility that i read and i highly recommend it Pregnancy Fertility awareness Friends Breastfeeding EastEnders Miscarriage Marilyn Monroe Lucille Ball Menstrual cycle In vitro fertilisation Sexual abstinence Infertility Abortion debate Apollo 8 Jon Secada Abortion The Lovely Bones God Emperor of Dune Charmed Knots Landing Sharon Tate Teenage pregnancy Neighbours Birth control Childbirth One Life to Live Oral contraceptive Time Out of Mind Phoebe Halliwell Twin Spina bifida Elvis and Me Sin City Social rule Abortion in the United States Marriage Obstetrics Avenue Q Days of our Lives Melanie Wilkes Only Fools and Horses Married... with Children Condom Cytomegalovirus Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Kodocha Mystique (comics) Human sexual behavior Jean Grey Pregnancy fetishism Transactional analysis Pitaten Fiddler on the Roof Guinea pig Autism Fire Emblem: Blazing Sword Scenes from a Memory The Handmaid's Tale Attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder Urinary incontinence Kate Vaiden Sexual revolution Similarities betwe